  <ManualInstallationSteps>
    <step>
      <Number>0</Number>
      <Title>Resolve all UI prompts</Title>
      <Instructions>All updates should be DISABLED.  Do NOT restart until the end of the manual installations. 
      Click "Finish" on all dialog boxes when installations are done.  Adobe fires up browsers and points to them to Adobe site.  Close those browsers.  </Instructions>
    </step>

    <step>
      <Number>1</Number>
      <Title>Delete Paths</Title>
      <Instructions>In the installation folder of the ops.exe, as an administrator, execute DeletePaths.bat.  This will delete all the shortcuts</Instructions>
    </step>

    <step>
      <Number>2</Number>
      <Title>Move Nivio bits to program files.</Title>
      <Instructions>The bits should already be present in the ops.exe folder.  The zip file is NivioProgramfiles.zip. 
      1) Unzip the content to a directory.
      2) Copy the the NivioTemp folder to c:\Program Files
      3) Rename NivioTemp to Nivio
      </Instructions>
    </step>

    <step>
      <Number>100</Number>
      <Title>Push McAfee Virus Scan Enterprise agent from EPO Management Server</Title>
      <Instructions>
        Need to get together with a Sys Admin. for this.
        1) Login to EPO Server->EPO Mgmt Console->SystemTree->Groups->Add New System
        2) Remove Shortcut from all user profile.
      </Instructions>
    </step>

    <step>
      <Number>200</Number>
      <Title>Configure RDS Services</Title>
      <Instructions>
        Add Role :- Remote Desktop Session Host
        Add User :- Add domain user
        Experience:-  Client Experience Feature Sound Redirection,
        Add RDS Appropriate Licensing Server (ex C1-SQLMR01)"


      </Instructions>
    </step>

    <step>
      <Number>300</Number>
      <Title>Configure RDS Services</Title>
      <Instructions>

        Add User :- Add domain user
        Experience:-  Client Experience Feature Sound Redirection,
        Add RDS Appropriate Licensing Server (ex C1-SQLMR01)"


      </Instructions>
    </step>

    <step>
      <Number>400</Number>
      <Title>NAT/PAT Entry on firewall</Title>
      <Instructions>
        Make NAT/PAT Entry available on Firewall (8xxx for RDP/3389, 9xxx for Ericom/8080)

      </Instructions>
    </step>

    <step>
      <Number>500</Number>
      <Title>Nivio Performance Counter Setup</Title>
      <Instructions>

        (A) Change ConnectionSting for C1 in Configuration file. C:\Program Files(x86) \NivioPerformanceCounterSetup\ NivioPerformanceCounters.exe.config
        (B) Update Server  Details in NivioPCounters Database (NivioTSMapping2 Table) (like ServerName, Internal/External ServerIP, Port
        (C) Update TemplateID value to 1 in Nivio_server_status table
        Note: Recommended to have DBA available so that require changes can been done correctly in table
        
      </Instructions>
    </step>

    <step>
      <Number>600</Number>
      <Title>Make Terminal Server Available in Production/LB</Title>
      <Instructions>
        Update Server Details in Nivio Database (NivioTSMapping)
      </Instructions>
    </step>

   


    
  </ManualInstallationSteps>
